   },
   "source": [
    "## Step 3. Model Building, Step 4. Results and Evaluation\n",
    "- Fit a model that predicts the outcome variable using two or more independent variables\n",
    "- Check model assumptions\n",
    "- Evaluate the model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "QxCXjdpSaB8A"
   },
   "source": [
    "### Identify the type of prediction task."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "YcCoHhnKcEov"
   },
   "source": [
    "The prediction task involves classifying whether an employee is likely to leave the company or remain employed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "yeUlo3W0ais-"
   },
   "source": [
    "### Identify the types of models most appropriate for this task."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "A0Mo6f9tOchC"
   },
   "source": [
    "Both logistic regression and tree-based models, such as decision trees, random forests, or gradient boosting, are well-suited for this classification task. Given that there is a large sample size still remaining after data cleaning and there are no missing values we will use the decision tree based model XGBoost."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "Bf2BU6B1QmTg"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Recall model assumptions\n",
    "\n",
    "**XGBoost classifier assumptions**\n",
    "- Outcome variable can be categorical or continuous.\n",
    "- Observations should be independent of each other.\n",
    "- Features should have minimal multicollinearity.\n",
    "- Outliers are generally handled well but should be monitored.\n",
    "- No strict assumption of a linear relationship.\n",
    "- Sufficiently large sample size.\n",
    "- Features should contain minimal missing values."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "OrW2oXy4OfD1"
   },
   "source": [
    "### Modeling\n",
    "\n",
    "- Fit a model that predicts the outcome variable using two or more independent variables\n",
    "- Check model assumptions"
   ]
  },
